	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, for the umpteenth time, Yes. Casters mele. Not much, not often, not in serious battles, but it DOES come in handy. Particularly if you've taken a few mins to raise the skill up. Int casters do get a few decent weapons, particularly at higher levels. We also get a few haste items. Now like everything else in EQ you have to know WHEN to do it. Cleric gets aggro, DS yerself, overnuke to get the aggro, and mele it out till someone gets the aggro off you. Again, gotta know when and at what level range to do it, but it does come in handy. That's saying nothing of greeny whupping when you can't get a spell off.<br>Can save entire groups just by knowing WHEN to take the aggro and how long to hold it. In those situations, yer gonna mele whether you like it or not.<br><br>Just my 2cp.<br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, The Mad Mage of Povar<br><br><br>PS: If ya ARE gonna mele tho, this prolly isn't the weapon to do it with. Skill aside, the delay seems too high to get it to proc often enough to be used for anything other than greanie beating to regain life. 'course... I AM crazy... *shrug*<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Dec 23 05:54:05 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
